Above cases is from UT:https://github.com/PowerShell/psl-monad/blob/master/monad/tests/monad/DRT/commands/utility/UnitTests/FormatAndOutputTests.cs#L512

Add a PropertySet member with wrong type for Value1, no error send out.

```
        try
        {
            add-member -InputObject a PropertySet Name ImNotACollection
            Throw "Execution OK"
        }
        catch
        {
            $_.FullyQualifiedErrorId | Should Be "ConvertToFinalInvalidCastException,Microsoft.PowerShell.Commands.AddMemberCommand"
        }
```

Run **add-member** command below, since we didn't specify the Value, it should send a error out, but it didn't.

```
        $membersYouCannotAdd = "Method", "Property", "ParameterizedProperty", "AnythingElse"
        foreach ($member in $membersYouCannotAdd)
        {
            try
            {
                Add-Member -InputObject a $member Name  
                Throw "Execution OK"
            }
            catch
            {
                $_.FullyQualifiedErrorId | Should Be ""

            }
        }
```

After running Pester test code below,  the exception is 'Execution OK' rather than the desired one.

```
    It "Should be throw Exception when missing mandatory parameter -script" -Skip:($IsLinux -Or $IsOSX) {
        $ErrorActionPreference = "Stop"
        try {
            powershell.exe -noninteractive -command 'sbp -line 1' 
            Throw "Execution OK" 
        }
        catch {
            $_.FullyQualifiedErrorId | Should Be "MissingMandatoryParameter,Microsoft.PowerShell.Commands.SetPSBreakpointCommand"
        }
        $ErrorActionPreference = "SilentlyContinue"
    }
```

But when running command "powershell.exe -noninteractive -command 'sbp -line 1'" in our test environment, it throw the exception as expected: 
![capture](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/16587262/14481717/524a2876-0168-11e6-9529-c0927dc23ac0.JPG)

Fail to catch the exception if you put 'Should Throw' here:

```
 It "Fail to set psbreakpoints when script is a file of wrong type " {
    {
        $tempFile = [System.IO.Path]::GetTempFileName()
        Set-PSBreakpoint -Script $tempFile -Line 1 
    } | Should Throw
    } 
```

But it works if you put it as below:

```
    It "Fail to set psbreakpoints when script is a file of wrong type " {
        $tempFile = [System.IO.Path]::GetTempFileName()
        Set-PSBreakpoint -Script $tempFile -Line 1 
